'''Richard O'Neill''' (born 1943) is an Anglo-Irish author and editor.<ref name="Middle">{{cite book |title=Middle East abstracts |last=Library Information and Research Service |first= |authorlink= |author2=Aristarchus Knowledge Industries |year=2003 |publisher=Reference Corporation |location= |isbn= |page=41 |pages= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=874MAQAAMAAJ&q=%22Richard+O'Neill%22+%22military+history%22&dq=%22Richard+O'Neill%22+%22military+history%22&hl=en&ei=Ij4ZTvuPPMbYiAK99ITSBQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CDsQ6AEwAw |accessdate=July 10, 2011}}</ref> Formerly a regular soldier, itinerant labourer and professional boxer, he now specializes in military history and has contributed to many books on weaponry and military history, as well as writing on [[Victorian painting]]. He has a son and a daughter from a former marriage. He is now semi-retired and lives alone in coastal Suffolk.
==Bibliography== * ''The Complete Encyclopedia of 20th Century Warships'' * ''The Vietnam War'' * ''An Illustrated History of the Royal Navy'' * ''Presidents of the United States'' * ''The Middle Ages'' * ''World War II '' * ''Suicide Squads - the men and machines of World War II Special Operations'', Salamander Books, London, 1999 ISBN 1-84065-082-6<ref name="Middle"/><ref>{{cite news |title=Suicidal Weapons Of WWII Illustrated |author=Dick Peterson |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=gWpJAAAAIBAJ&sjid=0goNAAAAIBAJ&pg=6155,3412741&dq=richard-o-neill+suicide-squads&hl=en |newspaper=[[The Post and Courier]] |date=February 13, 1983 |accessdate=July 10, 2011}}</ref> * ''Natural Disasters'' * ''Paintings of Victorian Childhood'' * ''The Life and Work of Dante Gabriel Rossetti'' * ''Patrick O'Brian's Navy'' * ''Men and Monsters'' * ''Strange World''
